# Markdown Styling

## 01 Code
Use backticks for `inline code` or triple backticks for blocks:
```markdown
code block
```

## 02 Citations
Use footnotes for references:
```markdown
Text with reference[^1].
[^1]: Source URL or description.
```

## 03 Alerts
```markdown
> [!NOTE|TIP|IMPORTANT|WARNING|CAUTION]
> Alert content here.
```

## 04 Dropdowns
Use for optional verbose content:
```markdown
<details>
<summary><b>ℹ️ Alternative Names for Variable Elimination</b></summary>
<br />

- Bucket elimination
- Sum-product algorithm (in specific contexts)
- Non-serial dynamic programming
- Adaptive consistency
- Directional resolution

<br />
</details>
```

